   &quot;Good journey to you, Vasilissa,&quot; she murmered softly, then looked down in respect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonprincessriver>AmazonPrincessRiver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#993300>(1/29/03 1:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=424.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sad day...</span><hr size=1> The young Princess... she didn't want to think about the fact she would soon become queen... gently picked Zoe up and settled her on her hip.  She took a moment to adjust to the weight before stepping forward.  <br>
<br>
Gabrielle's legacy was clear in her poise even in this horrible moment, and the eloquence of her words.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Queen Gabrielle took me in, trusting so much more in my potential than I could dream.  I was a common village girl, unaware of my heritage and content to spend the rest of my life making carvings, but she showed me the way I was to follow.  The Amazon way.  I have the responsibility and the honor of living up to that, which I will thank her for in my thoughts every single day.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Her voice was cracking by the end, and she quickly turned to the body on the pyre before her emotions became overwhelming.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Goodbye, my mother and my queen,&quot; she said quietly.  &quot;May Artemis give you a peaceful journey to the Land of the Dead.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odessaofpaphos>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#993300>(1/30/03 6:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=424.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sad day...</span><hr size=1> Odessa nodded in agreement with Alysia. She knew very little about Gabrielle's social life, but she knew she was a great queen with an astonishing background. The fact that she was just a bard from Poteidaia, turning to being a life-long friend to Xena, Princess and then Queen, and then becoming Queen again. She kind of reminded her a little bit of her brother, seeing as Julian was or still partially is a bard.<br>
