<br>
As the grey ghost mare slowely strode to the hallowed grounds, a figure worn and weary sat quietly on it's back.  Her auburn hair carelessly tasseled, her old leather's decorated with new scars, Hippolyte's brown eyes seemed even more serious then they had ever before.  <br>
<br>
She stopped the mare about thirty feet behind the surrounding funeral party.  By the decorations on the pyre....it wasn't hard for Hippolyte to know who lay there..lit to rise to the Gods.  The once Vasilissa and now warrior's heart fell.  Her lips staying silent..as memories of Gabrielle rushed thru her mind.  Those she touched would feel a great loss....no matter how...they were touched. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
