<br>
She knew that her and River weren't blood sisters, but she loved her just the same.  She saw Gabrielle in River's face, which comforted her and brought her to nuzzle the bottom of River's chin with the top of her head.<br>
<br>
When they approached their mother's body tears began to sneak up again.  She gripped River's top where her little hands held onto her and light sniffles became more apparent. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Zoe</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, The mystic Lykastian Princess<br>
Daughter of the great battling bard, Gabrielle.<br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 725<br> <font color=#993300>(2/5/03 11:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=424.topic&index=35>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sadness...</span><hr size=1> The two younger amazons who clung to each other tightly caught Hippolyte's eyes.  She had not known either of them...but it was obvious the children were Gabrielle's.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Hera....be the motherless,&quot; Hippolyte whispered.  As she said that she thought of her own son, Theseus.  He was now living with Gabby's family.  Learning the ways of the world ruled by men.  He had grown up much, since he had moved to Poteidaia.  Hippolyte was proud.  He at least treated the women of the town with great respect.  And was in the process of becoming a great warrior.  <br>
<br>
Hipp's eyes turned to the pyre.  She wondered what had brought death to the beautiful bardic queen.  <br>
<br>
As her eyes continued to dance around the amazons who stood watching their parting sister.  Hippolyte saw Solari and DeLerium.  She smiled proudly at DeLerium....she even looked the magnificant Vasilissa of Themiscrya.  Her eyes glancing to Solari...she saw that she too, wore the belt signifying one as a Vasilissa.  One brow titled curiously, as she looked at the belts markings.  The markings looked to signify war.  Her face quickly frowned.  Was the Amazon Nation at war?  Is that why her father Ares sent her back home? <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
